"<div>\n<h2>Butter Shrimp and Mushroom with Cranberry Sauce Recipe</h2>\n<h3>Ingredients:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>1/2 cup butter, softened</li>\n<li>1 pound shrimp, peeled and deveined</li>\n<li>1 cup mushrooms, sliced</li>\n<li>1/2 cup sweetened cranberry sauce</li>\n<li>1/4 cup all-purpose flour</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Instructions:</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Melt 1/4 cup of butter in a pan over medium-high heat and sauté the shrimp until cooked through.</li>\n<li>Remove shrimp from pan and keep warm.</li>\n<li>In the same pan, add another 1/4 cup of butter and sauté the mushrooms until they are tender.</li>\n<li>Remove mushrooms from pan and keep warm.</li>\n<li>Add the remaining butter to the same pan and once melted, add the flour and cook for 1-2 minutes, stirring constantly until a roux is formed.</li>\n<li>Slowly whisk in the cranberry sauce and continue to stir until smooth and thickened.</li>\n<li>Add the cooked shrimp and mushrooms to the pan and stir until they are coated in the sauce and heated through.</li>\n<li>Serve hot and enjoy!</li>\n</ol>\n</div>"